🍕 Pizza Sales Data Analysis using SQL

This project focuses on analyzing pizza sales data to uncover meaningful business insights using SQL.
The dataset consists of multiple relational tables, including orders, 
order details, pizzas, and pizza types, enabling comprehensive analysis of sales performance and customer preferences.

Key objectives of this project:

Analyze overall sales and revenue performance
Identify most popular pizzas and categories
Understand customer ordering patterns (time, size, quantity)
Generate actionable business insights using SQL queries

🔧 Tools Used:

SQL (MySQL)
Excel (for visualization)
MS Word (for documentation)

📊 Key Analysis Performed:

Total orders and revenue calculation
Top-selling pizzas and highest-priced items
Category-wise and size-wise sales analysis
Time-based order distribution
Revenue contribution and cumulative sales trends
Advanced SQL queries using joins, aggregations, and window functions

📈 This project demonstrates strong skills in SQL, data analysis, and business insight generation, making it ideal for aspiring data analyst roles.
